happen to you while I'm here.

462
00:43:00,820 --> 00:43:02,386
OK.

463
00:43:02,448 --> 00:43:04,533
Good night, sweetie.

464
00:43:04,698 --> 00:43:07,495
- Good night, cookie.
- Good night, my angel cakes.

465
00:43:11,916 --> 00:43:13,586
Larry! Oh, honey...

466
00:43:13,751 --> 00:43:17,840
Well, I can't sleep. How do you like that?

467
00:43:18,006 --> 00:43:23,680
I have been in there tossing and turning
for hours. How about you, Sylvia?

468
00:43:23,846 --> 00:43:27,434
Yeah, I was thanking Larry
for a wonderful evening...

469
00:43:27,601 --> 00:43:32,524
and just saying how happy I am for you both.

470
00:43:32,690 --> 00:43:35,693
- Anyway... good night, Larry.
- Good night.

471
00:43:35,861 --> 00:43:38,405
- Good night, Vickie.
- Good night, Sylvia.

472
00:43:38,571 --> 00:43:40,824
See you in the morning for breakfast?

473
00:43:40,991 --> 00:43:42,869
- Yeah.
- Bye.

474
00:43:43,035 --> 00:43:44,600
Bye.

475
00:43:46,496 --> 00:43:48,333
Good night, honey.

476
00:43:48,499 --> 00:43:50,063
Good night, sweetheart.

477
00:44:11,108 --> 00:44:13,612
Beat it, while you're still healthy.

478
00:45:01,458 --> 00:45:03,000
- Jesus!
- Sh!

479
00:45:03,001 --> 00:45:06,254
Where you been? You're late.
I came looking for you.

480
00:45:06,422 --> 00:45:09,341
I couldn't get away. Where's the body?

481
00:45:09,508 --> 00:45:11,885
- I didn't know where to put her.
- Him.

482
00:45:12,052 --> 00:45:15,057
Him. He's in an empty bed on the second floor.

483
00:45:15,222 --> 00:45:19,102
Are you crazy? I can't have the police
snooping around this place.

484
00:45:19,269 --> 00:45:22,981
That's your problem. This is too risky.
Just pay me, I'm going.

485
00:45:23,149 --> 00:45:26,903
- You goofed up once today.
- Don't blame me.

486
00:45:27,069 --> 00:45:30,741
He was in a dress and a wig. How could I know?

487
00:45:30,907 --> 00:45:35,330
- You'll get your money when the job is done.
- I'll get my money tonight.

488
00:45:35,495 --> 00:45:39,459
Or I'll tell your whole family
what you're up to.

489
00:45:39,625 --> 00:45:44,006
You wouldn't know about the change
in the will if I hadn't told you.

490
00:45:44,173 --> 00:45:48,970
- I want Larry Abbot dead.
- Kill him yourself.

491
00:45:49,135 --> 00:45:55,352
You wouldn't have to hire people 
like me if you had the guts to kill...

492
00:46:14,290 --> 00:46:18,461
I'm all by myself and I'm very, very scared.

493
00:46:19,838 --> 00:46:23,091
Gee, ain't you a swell little duck?

494
00:46:23,258 --> 00:46:25,971
Are you afraid of werewolves?

495
00:46:26,136 --> 00:46:29,683
Are you kidding? The werewolf will eat me up.

496
00:46:29,850 --> 00:46:32,769
Would you like to give me a little kiss?

497
00:46:32,935 --> 00:46:35,355
I'm a little shy, but OK.

498
00:46:36,982 --> 00:46:43,656
Aren't you scared to be
in this great big house?

499
00:46:43,823 --> 00:46:49,621
What? Scared? Are you kidding? 
I'm not afraid of anything.

500
00:46:51,165 --> 00:46:54,210
- Uh-oh.
- Sh. Don't be frightened, Vickie.

501
00:46:54,377 --> 00:46:57,004
I need your help.

502
00:47:14,024 --> 00:47:15,588
Yuck.

503
00:47:20,532 --> 00:47:26,205
It's cold in here. Oh, what a day.

504
00:47:29,208 --> 00:47:33,464
Why, you little devil. You did it, didn't you?

505
00:47:34,798 --> 00:47:39,553
I didn't think you'd have 
the nerve. Oh, darling...

506
00:47:41,096 --> 00:47:44,017
What a great gift you're giving to me.

507
00:47:45,560 --> 00:47:48,772
I'll cherish this night for the rest of my life.

508
00:47:50,482 --> 00:47:55,739
Say, you're very quiet, aren't you?
What's the matter, honey?

509
00:47:55,905 --> 00:48:01,120
Are you shy? You want me 
to make the first move?

510
00:48:02,412 --> 00:48:04,373
Come here, cookie.

511
00:48:05,623 --> 00:48:08,586
Oh, honey...

512
00:48:11,923 --> 00:48:15,970
Want to play Donald?

513
00:48:17,137 --> 00:48:19,015
Oh, baby, oh...

514
00:48:20,224 --> 00:48:23,103
Go slow. Go slow, honey.

515
00:48:23,268 --> 00:48:25,314
Oh, sweetheart.

516
00:48:29,277 --> 00:48:33,865
Honey, your little body is frozen.

517
00:48:34,949 --> 00:48:36,994
Your legs are like ice.

518
00:48:38,704 --> 00:48:42,667
Well, maybe this'll warm you up.

519
00:48:49,716 --> 00:48:52,887
Pfister, thank goodness.
Something terrible has happened.

520
00:48:53,053 --> 00:48:56,225
- I found cousin Francis in my bed.
- Wearing a dress?

521
00:48:56,391 --> 00:48:57,600
Yes, he was.

522
00:48:57,601 --> 00:49:00,687
Ask him to leave. Say you have a headache.

523
00:49:00,853 --> 00:49:04,567
No, you don't understand.
Francis Junior is dead, do you hear?

524
00:49:04,734 --> 00:49:07,195
- He's dead.
- You must be mistaken, sir.

525
00:49:07,362 --> 00:49:09,906
No, come in here, please. I'll show you.

526
00:49:22,586 --> 00:49:28,135
- Do you see him?
- I think you'd better take a look, sir.

527
00:49:33,306 --> 00:49:37,020
- This can't be.
- I'm afraid so, sir.

528
00:49:37,187 --> 00:49:42,944
I'm telling you I felt a cold dead body
lying beside me in bed. Do you understand?

529
00:49:43,110 --> 00:49:46,948
I feel that every night. Warm brandy helps.

530
00:49:55,207 --> 00:49:58,670
- Are you sure you'll be all right, sir?
- Mm-hm.

531
00:49:58,836 --> 00:50:00,922
Good night, sir.

532
00:50:01,088 --> 00:50:04,384
Whoops, there goes my imagination again.

533
00:50:04,550 --> 00:50:08,973
- Beg pardon, sir?
- Nothing, Pfister, thanks. Good night.

534
00:50:09,139 --> 00:50:11,643
Good night, sir.

535
00:50:14,979 --> 00:50:19,067
Pleasant dreams.

536
00:50:26,867 --> 00:50:30,331
All right, no more nonsense.

537
00:50:30,497 --> 00:50:33,793
You were right, honey.
It was just my imagination.

538
00:50:42,677 --> 00:50:46,848
Now, you'd think this would frighten me.

539
00:50:47,975 --> 00:50:55,171
Well, it doesn't. Because I know that this is
just a filthy figment of my diseased imagination.

540
00:50:58,071 --> 00:51:04,995
And all I have to do to prove it
is simply reach out my hand...

541
00:51:12,252 --> 00:51:14,380
and touch it.

542
00:51:24,475 --> 00:51:29,231
Don't be a scaredy-cat. There's nothing there.

543
00:51:29,397 --> 00:51:31,734
Just touch it.

544
00:52:29,089 --> 00:52:30,654
Larry...

545
00:52:50,198 --> 00:52:52,409
Larry...

546
00:53:45,302 --> 00:53:47,472
Larry...

547
00:53:54,104 --> 00:53:56,398
Larry...

548
00:54:56,258 --> 00:54:58,761
What the hell's going on over there?

549
00:54:58,927 --> 00:55:02,598
- That's the Abbot place, isn't it?
- We better take a look.

550
00:55:29,044 --> 00:55:31,214
Ah! Who's that?

551
00:55:31,379 --> 00:55:33,758
- Pfister!
- Master Larry.

552
00:55:33,925 --> 00:55:37,138
Oh, thank goodness. Look, it's cousin Francis.

553
00:55:38,972 --> 00:55:40,388
He's dead!

554
00:55:40,389 --> 00:55:44,687
- That's what I was trying to tell you.
- You killed your own cousin.

555
00:55:44,854 --> 00:55:48,066
What? Remember I tried to show you a body?

556
00:55:48,232 --> 00:55:50,652
You're the werewolf. I've gotta tell your aunt.

557
00:55:50,818 --> 00:55:53,531
Wait a minute. Will you listen to me?

558
00:55:53,697 --> 00:55:57,952
- Somebody killed him and dragged him here.
- You did, you fiend.

559
00:55:58,118 --> 00:56:01,539
Are you crazy? Will you let me explain to you?

560
00:56:01,705 --> 00:56:05,169
There's something fishy
going on here and I don't like it.

561
00:56:05,334 --> 00:56:09,131
Now please stop eating
and tell me if everything's all right.

562
00:56:09,298 --> 00:56:12,218
- Murderer!
- Yes, everything's fine.

563
00:56:12,385 --> 00:56:16,724
- What was that?
- My husband in the cellar, drunk as usual.

564
00:56:16,889 --> 00:56:21,353
Oh, yeah? Well, I think we'd better
take a look ourselves.

565
00:56:23,563 --> 00:56:26,693
Thank you for the cake, ma'am.

566
00:56:26,859 --> 00:56:30,197
You've got the disease,
the curse of the werewolf.

567
00:56:30,363 --> 00:56:32,991
The beast is in your blood.

568
00:56:33,159 --> 00:56:34,723
Ow!

569
00:56:42,253 --> 00:56:44,463
- Hold it right there.
- What?

570
00:56:44,631 --> 00:56:48,802
- Just keep sitting right where you are.
- Sitting?

571
00:56:48,968 --> 00:56:51,429
Oh... All right.

572
00:56:51,597 --> 00:56:53,724
We heard some hollering down here.

573
00:56:53,889 --> 00:56:55,726
Oh, you mean...

574
00:56:58,436 --> 00:57:04,402
You filthy beast! I'll kill you! Murderer!

575
00:57:06,154 --> 00:57:12,036
- You some kind of crackpot?
- No, I was just going over my lines.

576
00:57:12,203 --> 00:57:15,415
- Who are you?
- Larry Abbot. My aunt lives here.

577
00:57:15,582 --> 00:57:20,378
Larry Abbot? Holy smokes.
You mean the radio actor?

578
00:57:20,546 --> 00:57:24,134
Yeah, that's me. I was just going over my lines.

579
00:57:29,139 --> 00:57:31,225
Murderer!

580
00:57:32,308 --> 00:57:36,189
You have to get it right
or the audience won't believe you.

581
00:57:36,356 --> 00:57:39,233
- That was you we heard?
- That was me.

582
00:57:39,401 --> 00:57:45,866
I didn't want to disturb the folks upstairs
so I came down here to sit and relax and...

583
00:57:48,701 --> 00:57:52,291
...go over my lines.
- What brings you here, Mr Abbot?

584
00:57:52,457 --> 00:57:53,707
Getting married.

585
00:57:53,708 --> 00:57:56,086
- Really?
- Yeah, finally gonna do it.

586
00:57:56,253 --> 00:58:00,758
- You boys must know her. Vickie Pearle.
- Hey, that's exciting.

587
00:58:00,925 --> 00:58:06,890
Yes, sir. It's the biggest thrill of my life,
I can tell you that. What the...?

588
00:58:07,057 --> 00:58:10,853
- What are you doing, Mr Abbot?
- Rats. Something terrible.

589
00:58:11,019 --> 00:58:14,106
It's the only drawback really
to rehearsing down here.

590
00:58:14,272 --> 00:58:17,861
Have you seen the butler?
He's supposed to be down here.

591
00:58:18,027 --> 00:58:20,990
No, no... I haven't seen him.

592
00:58:21,156 --> 00:58:24,827
Ho, ho, ho, ho, ho. Forget your 
troubles, come on, get happy.

593
00:58:25,034 --> 00:58:28,415
We're gonna chase all your blues away.
Boo, boo, shout hallelujah.

594
00:58:28,581 --> 00:58:31,167
Come on, get happy. Get...

595
00:58:32,210 --> 00:58:34,171
ready for the judgement day.

596
00:58:36,841 --> 00:58:40,220
Oh. I have to sing in next week's program.

597
00:58:40,386 --> 00:58:45,059
If you don't mind, I'll take a look around
before we go, for safety's sake.

598
00:58:45,225 --> 00:58:47,769
- Sure.
- Well, good night for now.

599
00:58:47,936 --> 00:58:49,185
Good night.

600
00:58:49,186 --> 00:58:53,193
- Night, Mr Abbot.
- Good night, nice of you boys to drop by.

601
00:58:53,358 --> 00:58:54,923
Murderer!

602
00:58:56,195 --> 00:58:59,450
That was phoney. Murderer...

603
00:58:59,615 --> 00:59:01,326
Mmm... better.

604
00:59:01,493 --> 00:59:03,870
Why, you filthy beast.

605
00:59:04,039 --> 00:59:06,792
- Come on, Bill.
- I'll kill you. Murd...

606
00:59:14,091 --> 00:59:19,138
That was a close call. Poor old Pfister.

607
00:59:19,305 --> 00:59:23,936
Sorry I had to hit you, old fella.
How you doing?

608
00:59:24,101 --> 00:59:28,941
Pfister, do you know where Vickie is?
Pfister, can you hear me?

609
00:59:29,108 --> 00:59:32,905
- Pardon.
- Oh, dear.

610
01:00:19,457 --> 01:00:23,003
Who is it? Who's there? Is someone there?

611
01:00:23,211 --> 01:00:25,380
Pfister, is that you?

612
01:00:36,852 --> 01:00:41,941
Madam Kate was right. I saw it.

613
01:00:42,108 --> 01:00:45,403
- You saw what, you drunken sot?
- The werewolf.

614
01:00:45,570 --> 01:00:47,656
- What?
- It wasn't Master Larry.

615
01:00:47,823 --> 01:00:51,952
What are you babbling about?
The police were here. Did you know that?

616
01:00:52,117 --> 01:00:54,330
- I've got to hide Master Francis.
- What?

617
01:00:54,496 --> 01:00:57,041
Master Larry's innocent. I must hide that body.

618
01:00:57,209 --> 01:00:59,211
- Give me that.
- It's mine.

619
01:00:59,376 --> 01:01:02,297
- Give it to me.
- It's my last one.

620
01:01:02,463 --> 01:01:04,258
Pull free.

621
01:01:05,885 --> 01:01:09,723
"When the wine runneth red,
it biteth like a serpent".

622
01:01:21,860 --> 01:01:24,031
Vickie!

623
01:01:37,587 --> 01:01:40,425
Vickie!

624
01:01:40,590 --> 01:01:42,259
Larry...

625
01:01:42,426 --> 01:01:44,553
Ow, this thing's pinching my butt.

626
01:01:44,719 --> 01:01:48,475
Just hang on for a minute, 
Vickie. Hang on. God!

627
01:01:48,641 --> 01:01:52,771
I should never have let your 
father talk me into this.

628
01:01:52,938 --> 01:01:58,695
Vickie, would you hold still, please?
I can't control this if you move around.

629
01:01:58,860 --> 01:02:03,367
If you want my opinion, I think
this Strickland thing is a lot of baloney.

630
01:02:03,533 --> 01:02:05,244
Ow!

631
01:02:05,410 --> 01:02:08,539
- Could you let me down for a minute?
- Why?

632
01:02:08,705 --> 01:02:11,668
- I gotta go to the powder room.
- Vickie!

633
01:02:11,834 --> 01:02:15,297
I gotta go to the can. What should I do?

634
01:02:15,463 --> 01:02:18,091
Hold still. Just hold still.

635
01:02:18,257 --> 01:02:20,761
All right. This is gonna be some wedding.

636
01:02:20,928 --> 01:02:24,807
A loony for a husband
and Peter Pan for his wife.

637
01:03:16,157 --> 01:03:22,164
- Isn't it nice Mr Abbot's getting married?
- Shut up and keep your eyes open.

638
01:03:22,329 --> 01:03:25,126
What are they looking for?
They could ruin things.

639
01:03:25,293 --> 01:03:29,048
- Dr Strickland didn't have the police, did he?
- I could kill them!

640
01:03:29,213 --> 01:03:33,595
- Don't worry, Dad. There's plenty of time.
- There is not.

641
01:04:10,094 --> 01:04:13,848
- That's my lightning machine.
- Where's Vickie?

642
01:04:14,013 --> 01:04:18,145
- She's in the powder room.
- What is that supposed to mean?

643
01:04:18,312 --> 01:04:20,355
I assume she's powdering her nose.

644
01:04:24,652 --> 01:04:27,698
- There's something fishy here.
- That came from the garden.

645
01:04:27,864 --> 01:04:29,824
Come on.

646
01:04:52,934 --> 01:04:56,187
- Pfister!
- Master Larry, you did frighten me.

647
01:04:56,354 --> 01:04:58,731
- What have you got there?
- The other body.

648
01:04:58,899 --> 01:05:01,444
- What other body?
- He was under your cousin.

649
01:05:01,611 --> 01:05:03,529
I was about to bury them.

650
01:05:03,697 --> 01:05:09,535
- Hey, what's going on over there?
- Get rid of the bodies! They'll think I did it.

651
01:05:10,495 --> 01:05:13,999
- They must be around here somewhere.
- There!

652
01:05:14,167 --> 01:05:17,545
Hey, who are you people? What are you doing?

653
01:05:17,712 --> 01:05:21,716
- Stay right where you are.
- We got you covered, so no fast moves.

654
01:05:23,510 --> 01:05:25,388
What the...?

655
01:05:26,013 --> 01:05:30,059
- Mr Abbot.
- Hello there. What a beautiful night, isn't it?

656
01:05:30,227 --> 01:05:32,520
Isn't it romantic?

657
01:05:32,687 --> 01:05:37,317
Drifting shadows write the oldest magic word

658
01:05:37,483 --> 01:05:41,781
Oh, to be dancing with the woman 
you love, just before the wedding.

659
01:05:42,866 --> 01:05:45,076
Darling...

660
01:05:50,249 --> 01:05:53,878
The woman you love? You mean, this is...

661
01:05:54,044 --> 01:05:56,965
Boys, meet Vickie Pearle.

662
01:05:57,131 --> 01:06:02,013
How do you do, Miss Pearle?
Holy mackerel, wait till I tell the kids.

663
01:06:02,179 --> 01:06:04,640
Gosh, could I trouble you for an autograph?

664
01:06:04,807 --> 01:06:07,184
Well...

665
01:06:07,351 --> 01:06:11,857
- Am I imposing too much, Mr Abbot?
- No, that's all right.

666
01:06:12,023 --> 01:06:14,526
- Do you have pencil and paper?
- Sure.

667
01:06:14,694 --> 01:06:17,739
- What's your name?
- Bill.

668
01:06:17,905 --> 01:06:20,116
All right.

669
01:06:20,283 --> 01:06:25,371
Could you hold the pad steady,
please? There you go, Bill.

670
01:06:25,540 --> 01:06:29,294
Thanks, Mr Abbot. That's awfully nice of you.

671
01:06:29,459 --> 01:06:35,132
- Quite all right, Bill.
- We'll leave you two lovebirds alone now.

672
01:06:35,299 --> 01:06:42,392
Come on, Mickey. Weren't they nice?
I love show folks. They're so full of life.

673
01:06:45,395 --> 01:06:48,231
I'm ready, Charles.

674
01:06:53,027 --> 01:06:55,322
Charles?

675
01:06:56,448 --> 01:06:59,118
Charlie? Hey, where'd everybody go?

676
01:06:59,285 --> 01:07:03,332
I woke up in the woodbin
and saw you go to the kitchen.

677
01:07:03,498 --> 01:07:06,418
Then this fiend crossed straight in front of me.

678
01:07:06,584 --> 01:07:08,421
He couldn't have been more than...

679
01:07:09,506 --> 01:07:11,069
Oh my! Pfister!

680
01:07:13,384 --> 01:07:14,885
Help! Someone help!

681
01:07:14,886 --> 01:07:17,723
He couldn't have been more than what?

682
01:07:40,749 --> 01:07:43,669
Paul! Francis!

683
01:07:46,339 --> 01:07:48,842
Charles!

684
01:08:26,134 --> 01:08:29,054
Whoever your werewolf is, he's gone now.

685
01:08:29,221 --> 01:08:33,935
I saw him just a few moments ago.
He was standing right here.

686
01:08:34,100 --> 01:08:37,898
Aunt Kate, don't start again
about one of us being a werewolf.

687
01:08:38,064 --> 01:08:41,276
This is the 20th century.
People don't become werewolves.

688
01:08:41,442 --> 01:08:44,113
Are you so sure?

689
01:08:44,280 --> 01:08:48,242
- Excuse me. I want to see who they are.
- Don't!

690
01:08:48,409 --> 01:08:52,456
I'm sorry, Francis. Your son is dead.

691
01:08:52,623 --> 01:08:56,669
- He's been murdered.
- Oh, my God.

692
01:08:58,253 --> 01:09:02,467
- Oh, dear God in heaven!
- I'm so sorry, Francis.

693
01:09:02,634 --> 01:09:05,553
- Who was the other man?
- We don't know, Francis.

694
01:09:06,679 --> 01:09:09,684
Dr Abbot. Where's Larry?

695
01:09:09,850 --> 01:09:14,355
- Aunt Kate saw him here with a werewolf.
- Cut the bullshit.

696
01:09:14,523 --> 01:09:18,485
I just want to know where Larry is.

697
01:09:18,652 --> 01:09:24,325
I don't know where Larry is.
If I did I'd tell you, I swear to God.

698
01:09:34,210 --> 01:09:37,131
- There's a homicidal maniac loose.
- Where are the police?

699
01:09:37,297 --> 01:09:40,552
- They're gone. I saw them leave.
- Should I call them?

700
01:09:40,719 --> 01:09:43,346
Yes, you'd better. All right, let's spread out.

701
01:09:43,513 --> 01:09:48,852
- Men check the grounds, the women inside.
- Come with me while I call the police.

702
01:09:49,021 --> 01:09:51,272
- Kate.
- Go on, find Larry.

703
01:09:51,439 --> 01:09:53,984
I'll stay here with Pfister. Go on.

704
01:09:54,151 --> 01:09:56,695
- Are you sure?
- Go on, go on.

705
01:10:27,606 --> 01:10:31,735
Larry, stop whimpering.
Stand up straight like a big boy.

706
01:10:31,900 --> 01:10:35,447
You've got to help Mummy.
This is a very special day.

707
01:10:35,613 --> 01:10:38,285
Look at your tie. It's all twisted again.

708
01:10:38,451 --> 01:10:41,745
Try to keep it straight, honey.
Just a little while longer.

709
01:10:41,913 --> 01:10:46,001
I don't want anything to go wrong today.

710
01:10:48,628 --> 01:10:52,633
What are you afraid of? That old lightning?

711
01:10:52,800 --> 01:10:57,598
Lightning can't hurt you, honey.
Everyone knows that.

712
01:11:46,236 --> 01:11:50,866
I know it's late, Officer,
but this is an emergency.

713
01:11:52,368 --> 01:11:55,955
No. No, I'm not imagining things.

714
01:11:57,708 --> 01:12:01,712
I don't care how many times
you've been out here already!

715
01:12:01,879 --> 01:12:03,839
Two people have been murdered.

716
01:12:04,006 --> 01:12:08,678
Is that important enough for a phone call
in the middle of the night?

717
01:12:08,845 --> 01:12:14,393
Get out here or I'm calling the mayor.
You'll be looking for a job by the morning.

718
01:12:14,560 --> 01:12:18,439
OK. We'll see you in a few minutes, then.

719
01:12:21,777 --> 01:12:26,448
That guy got me angry.
Still, they'll be here in a couple of minutes.

720
01:12:26,616 --> 01:12:29,077
So why don't you just relax, huh?

721
01:12:30,870 --> 01:12:34,499
What's the matter? What are you staring at?

722
01:12:34,665 --> 01:12:40,881
- Nothing. You were so angry. Good for you.
- Oh, yeah. Here.

723
01:12:56,564 --> 01:12:59,820
Larry isn't the only actor in the family.

724
01:13:09,372 --> 01:13:14,544
- You filthy, murdering skunk.
- I was just trying to earn a buck.

725
01:14:38,348 --> 01:14:41,977
I'm the good boy, not cousin Larry.

726
01:14:43,728 --> 01:14:46,190
I'm smarter than cousin Larry.

727
01:14:47,734 --> 01:14:51,530
I'm better-looking than cousin Larry.

728
01:14:52,656 --> 01:14:56,243
And I'm gonna be a hell of a lot richer.

729
01:15:10,427 --> 01:15:16,475
That vase cost me 5,000 dollars.
There are only three like it in the world.

730
01:15:16,641 --> 01:15:20,479
- Two.
- You... Two.

731
01:15:20,645 --> 01:15:22,982
Hold this. Oh, well.

732
01:15:25,110 --> 01:15:26,673
Oh.

733
01:15:28,363 --> 01:15:32,451
- Darling...
- Let's get on with this wedding, my dears.

734
01:15:33,702 --> 01:15:37,916
And do you, Vickie Pearle, take this 
man to love, honour and cherish...

735
01:15:38,082 --> 01:15:41,211
- until death do you part?
- I do.

736
01:15:41,376 --> 01:15:47,718
I now pronounce you man and wife.
You may kiss the bride.

737
01:15:53,766 --> 01:15:56,145
Wait! Oh, wait.

738
